\begin{align*}\bullet&\;\;\;1<|Z(G)|<p^n\\ \bullet&\;\;\;\text{Inn}\,(G)\cong G/Z(G)\;\;\text{and this last group cannot be cyclic non-trivial, thus}\\ \bullet&\;\;\;|\text{Inn}\,(G)|=p^k\;,\;\;1<k<n\\ \bullet&\;\;\;\text{By Cauchy's theorem there exists an element of order $\,p\,$ in}\;\;\text{Inn}\,(G)\le\text{Aut}\,(G)\end{align*}
